Not to get metaphysical
or anything,

1:18:33.576 --> 1:18:36.243
but I had an inspiration.

1:18:37.847 --> 1:18:42.950
And it does feel
kind of... divine.

1:18:43.820 --> 1:18:45.119
Divine?

1:18:45.855 --> 1:18:47.121
Well.

1:18:48.057 --> 1:18:49.924
I was thinking...

1:18:52.061 --> 1:18:55.463
[sighs] maybe if we had
a yard sale.

1:18:56.399 --> 1:18:58.132
My stuff and yours.

1:19:00.336 --> 1:19:02.103
We could make
a weekend of it.

1:19:02.705 --> 1:19:05.906
I did some research.
People can make
a lot of money.

1:19:05.908 --> 1:19:10.845
But even if we don't,
I have a feeling.

1:19:13.082 --> 1:19:17.818
What happened when you were
in the hospital?

1:19:19.589 --> 1:19:21.188
What happened?

1:19:22.592 --> 1:19:25.159
Did you see the light?

1:19:26.562 --> 1:19:28.162
The light?
You know.

1:19:29.298 --> 1:19:30.498
The light.

1:19:32.101 --> 1:19:34.502
I don't--
I don't think so.

1:19:35.471 --> 1:19:37.271
I just have a feeling.

1:19:39.776 --> 1:19:41.842
I don't mean to upset you.

1:19:44.380 --> 1:19:46.213
I'm not upset.

1:19:46.749 --> 1:19:48.382
Well, you sound upset.

1:19:49.786 --> 1:19:51.352
I'm not upset.

1:19:53.422 --> 1:19:57.992
It's just I--
I had a feeling, too.

1:20:00.296 --> 1:20:05.232
Maybe it's not divine
like you, but...

1:20:07.136 --> 1:20:09.136
I have a feeling, too.

1:20:19.315 --> 1:20:22.082
[man on TV, indistinct]
[Ed] Oh, not him.

1:20:22.752 --> 1:20:23.951
[man #2 on TV, indistinct]

1:20:23.953 --> 1:20:25.653
[grunts]

1:20:25.655 --> 1:20:27.321
Oh, I love her.

1:20:27.323 --> 1:20:29.123
<i> ...and then, they</i>
<i> were off to Florence.</i>

1:20:29.125 --> 1:20:31.192
She always looks so classy.

1:20:31.828 --> 1:20:34.628
[newscaster on TV]
<i> There were TVs on the train,</i>
<i> there were diplomats,</i>

1:20:34.630 --> 1:20:36.997
<i> there were Americans,</i>
<i> there were Parisians,</i>

1:20:36.999 --> 1:20:39.567
<i> there were Syrian refugees.</i>

1:20:39.936 --> 1:20:41.735
<i> Everyone traveled together</i>

1:20:42.171 --> 1:20:45.239
<i> on the way to Florence.</i>

1:20:45.942 --> 1:20:48.275
Why? That's interesting.

1:20:48.277 --> 1:20:51.478
I thought you always say
we should keep up
on current events.

1:20:51.480 --> 1:20:53.848
Current events?
You want current events?

1:20:54.217 --> 1:20:57.251
Well, you're not gonna
find it there.
That woman is a liar.

1:20:58.721 --> 1:21:04.225
A lying, dishonest, disloyal,
opportunistic liar...

1:21:04.227 --> 1:21:07.161
[Ronnie] Huh.
...that one day will realize
what she did.

1:21:07.163 --> 1:21:09.196
And then, she'll regret it,
I can promise you that.

1:21:09.198 --> 1:21:12.199
Why do you say that?
You don't even know her.

1:21:12.201 --> 1:21:14.435
[laughs]
Oh, I know her, all right.

1:21:17.073 --> 1:21:18.706
She's my ex-wife.

1:21:20.543 --> 1:21:21.775
Your wife?

1:21:22.478 --> 1:21:26.313
[Ed] My ex-wife.
She left a long time ago.

1:21:26.315 --> 1:21:29.149
[grunting] Nineteen years.

1:21:29.552 --> 1:21:32.152
What, she's--
she's Brian's mother?

1:21:32.722 --> 1:21:34.088
[chuckles] Yeah.

1:21:34.657 --> 1:21:36.090
He's a genuine son of a bitch.

1:21:36.092 --> 1:21:39.226
Ed. Don't talk like that.

1:21:39.228 --> 1:21:40.327
Funny.

1:21:40.930 --> 1:21:43.964
[sighs] I still
watch her every day.

1:21:46.369 --> 1:21:50.671
She'll always
mean something to you.
It's okay.

1:21:52.008 --> 1:21:53.474
[sighs]

1:21:56.746 --> 1:21:58.178
Sunday.

1:21:58.614 --> 1:22:02.116
It's the best day
for a yard sale.
I looked it up.

1:22:03.386 --> 1:22:06.654
This Sunday?
Yeah. It's as good
as any Sunday.

1:22:08.090 --> 1:22:09.590
But what about...

1:22:11.460 --> 1:22:12.660
It's time.

1:22:15.097 --> 1:22:16.430
You know...

1:22:17.433 --> 1:22:21.635
we can start organizing
your stuff on Tuesday.

1:22:22.305 --> 1:22:24.171
If it's okay with you.

1:22:26.943 --> 1:22:28.809
What do you do
if your boyfriend

1:22:28.811 --> 1:22:33.147
who you really,
really care about
wants you to do something...

1:22:35.284 --> 1:22:37.985
that you just feel
uncomfortable about?

1:22:38.487 --> 1:22:41.355
I'd have to say it depends.
How bad is it?

1:22:43.125 --> 1:22:44.491
Well...

1:22:46.262 --> 1:22:48.462
Well, now I really
want to know what it is.

1:22:50.633 --> 1:22:52.032
Forget it.

1:22:55.938 --> 1:23:00.674
Never let a man
make you do something
you don't want to do.

1:23:04.280 --> 1:23:06.547
[line ringing]

1:23:17.660 --> 1:23:19.560
[knocking]

1:23:26.669 --> 1:23:28.402
[knocking continues]

1:23:58.000 --> 1:24:00.267
[chattering]

1:24:17.686 --> 1:24:20.254
-Why don't you answer my calls?
-I'm working.

1:24:20.256 --> 1:24:22.222
I know you're working.
I can see you're working.

1:24:22.224 --> 1:24:23.690
Why don't you answer my calls?

1:24:23.692 --> 1:24:25.893
[Ronnie] Please, not here.
Yes, here.

1:24:25.895 --> 1:24:27.995
You won't come to
me, I have to come to you.

1:24:27.997 --> 1:24:29.363
[whispers]
You don't understand.

1:24:29.365 --> 1:24:30.531
Then explain it to me.

1:24:30.533 --> 1:24:32.699
No, I can't explain it to you.

1:24:32.701 --> 1:24:37.271
Even if I could,
you wouldn't understand.
I don't understand.

1:24:37.273 --> 1:24:39.173
You said
you would do it with me.

1:24:39.175 --> 1:24:41.108
I didn't say
I would do it with you.

1:24:41.110 --> 1:24:43.310
-You did!
-Keep you voice down.

1:24:45.081 --> 1:24:47.681
Why is it so important to you
what I do?

1:24:47.683 --> 1:24:49.917
Because it's what
we talked about.
It's for us.

1:24:49.919 --> 1:24:51.418
No, it's for you.

1:24:51.420 --> 1:24:54.721
I'm fine where I am.
I'm good where I am.

1:24:54.723 --> 1:24:56.423
No, you're not.

1:24:56.425 --> 1:25:00.928
[gasping] Don't you presume
to tell me about me, Ed Hemsler.

1:25:00.930 --> 1:25:05.132
I am a grown woman,
and I don't have to
listen to you.

1:25:05.134 --> 1:25:06.700
I didn't say
you had to listen to me.

1:25:06.702 --> 1:25:08.235
Just get out.
Now, just a minute.

1:25:08.237 --> 1:25:10.170
-Get out!
-Is there a problem?

1:25:10.940 --> 1:25:13.640
Well, there's no problem.
Ed was just leaving.

1:25:17.880 --> 1:25:19.713
I thought this was for real.

1:25:24.086 --> 1:25:25.385
[grumbles]

1:26:04.260 --> 1:26:06.994
[Brian on phone]<i> She asked</i>
<i>how you were doing, so I said,</i>

1:26:06.996 --> 1:26:09.329
<i> "You remember when you</i>
<i> broke up with Sam?"</i>

1:26:09.331 --> 1:26:10.631
[Ed] Sam?

1:26:10.633 --> 1:26:12.099
<i>It was her boyfriend for, like,</i>

1:26:12.101 --> 1:26:13.834
<i> two weeks in eighth grade.</i>

1:26:13.836 --> 1:26:16.003
<i>But anyway, we're there talking,</i>
<i>and it was probably</i>
<i>the first time</i>

1:26:16.005 --> 1:26:20.007
<i>that I really opened up about</i>
<i>what it was like</i>
<i>when you and Mom were splitting.</i>

1:26:20.009 --> 1:26:21.308
<i> All the door-slamming.</i>

1:26:21.310 --> 1:26:23.043
<i> Like, that was your last word,</i>

1:26:23.045 --> 1:26:25.179
<i> but it never was,</i>

1:26:25.181 --> 1:26:27.347
<i> and I was just sitting there</i>
<i> like a...</i>

1:26:27.349 --> 1:26:30.584
<i> And then one day,</i>
<i> the doors stopped slamming,</i>
<i> and she was gone.</i>

1:26:32.188 --> 1:26:33.587
<i> Hey, Dad?</i>

1:26:33.822 --> 1:26:35.088
I'm here.

1:26:35.324 --> 1:26:37.191
<i> Look, all I'm saying</i>

1:26:37.193 --> 1:26:39.026
<i> is that sometimes</i>
<i> it can feel like</i>

1:26:39.028 --> 1:26:40.694
<i> you're losing everything,</i>

1:26:40.696 --> 1:26:43.463
<i>but really, you're not losing,</i>
<i>you're gaining.</i>

1:26:45.234 --> 1:26:47.034
Or at least,
that's what you taught me.

1:26:50.973 --> 1:26:52.539
I taught you that?

1:26:54.543 --> 1:26:56.476
Well, not in so many words.

1:26:57.913 --> 1:26:59.379
But yeah.

1:27:00.082 --> 1:27:01.748
[chuckles]

1:27:03.219 --> 1:27:06.920
[sighs] So, what else
did I teach you?

1:27:20.269 --> 1:27:22.603
[chimes]

1:28:52.695 --> 1:28:54.394
[grunts]

1:29:39.675 --> 1:29:40.907
[man] How you doing today?

1:29:40.909 --> 1:29:43.043
[chattering]

1:30:04.032 --> 1:30:05.732
[Ronnie] Excuse me?

1:30:13.342 --> 1:30:14.741
How much is this?

1:30:23.585 --> 1:30:24.851
That depends.

1:30:26.221 --> 1:30:27.954
How much is it worth to you?

1:30:29.258 --> 1:30:31.992
Oh... Not as much as I thought.

1:30:34.963 --> 1:30:39.766
Well, maybe somebody else
might need it more than you.

1:30:40.636 --> 1:30:45.672
Yeah, maybe. You never know
when you might need
a pretty jar.

1:30:50.212 --> 1:30:52.279
You're my BFF.

1:30:53.115 --> 1:30:56.283
My granddaughter told me
what that means.

1:30:56.285 --> 1:30:58.552
Best friend forever.

1:31:07.963 --> 1:31:10.230
[explosion]

1:31:10.232 --> 1:31:12.532
[rumbling]

1:32:14.830 --> 1:32:17.764
["Muskrat Love" playing]
